reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My 3 yr old loves this. It took him maybe 20-30 tries to finally get the strength/stamina to pump the trigger but once he did they are really fun. They all fly differently. Orange one does circles (not as fun in my opinion) and the other 2 fly in a more direct path. The light up feature is cool but I’m not a huge fan of the wires just being taped to the outside. Not dangerous or anything per se just not clean and secured.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Broke after a couple uses
reviews.reviewText: This is a fun toy. The original launcher broke after just a few uses. The company reached out after seeing my review and offered to send a new toy, stating that improvements had been made to improve the quality. The new one came today and it is awesome. Seems to launch the planes farther and it does feel heavier and higher quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewText: A bit on the cheap side but the 5 year old loved it. Lights up too! Great price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great buy, great price
reviews.reviewText: These came for Christmas, but the tail wing was missing. I wrote to the company. They send another box right away so my grandson didn't have to be without it for long. I returned the product as they requested. These are still going after strong. They've been caught in trees, flown over fences, and landed on roofs. I'm going to purchase a couple to give as gifts.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Easy to break
reviews.reviewText: I had to buy 2 of these. I bought it for my grandson's birthday in April. As soon as it was ready to shoot, it broke. He pulled the trigger and it broke. I mean talk about wasted money. I couldn't send it back because it broke when using. I just bought another one and called it a day. If you buy for a 6 yr old, make sure he pulls that Tigger with a delicate touch.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are so much fun and my grandson loves them!
reviews.reviewText: These are fun, and easy to use. But 1 day in my grandson snapped off the back of one plane trying to pull the trigger back to shoot it. That's why I didn't give it 5 stars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Little tough to pull back for the 2 year old but my 3.5 loves it! :-)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Although this was a last min fluff gift for my 9yr olds birthday, he only got to play with it twice b4 they fell apart. Glue that held the top of the plane to the foam body pulled apart almost immediately, and unfortunately I don't own a glue gun to repair it, so it went in the garbage the next month. Heed this review, these are cheaply made and unless u want to deal with fixing them after a few uses, don't waste the money!
